main event: Civilian observers reported seeing a luminous, strange and gray object with a dark edge that was observed rising along the eastern horizon and moving slowly westward over Richland, Washington on November 26, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed for periods of 18 to 26 minutes over a time span of about 3.5 hours.
The object was described as being half-dollar size with the naked eye and baseball-size through a telescope.
The object was observed changing colors from orange with the naked eye to orange and gray through the telescope.
The object was reported to stop at times during its steady, east-to-west course.
The observers noted the object was still high in the sky near midnight when they retired for the night.
sighted object: a luminous, strange and gray object with a dark edge
